{"uid":"7292276382661ad5","name":"[BUG-SF-007] TC-SF-013 — GET /api/v1/fetch/status with Accept: application/xml returns 500 (must be 406)","fullName":"oauth-token-spr-fetcher-api.spec.ts:1311:7","historyId":"2a63cd8ad170fd5762d8b5daa25b2ed7:ce104b03da2b5d4a8426255a65f4618e","time":{"start":1782954375553,"stop":1782954435751,"duration":60198},"description":"**[KNOWN BUG — BUG-SF-007]**\n\n**What this test does:**\nSends GET /api/v1/fetch/status with \"Accept: application/xml\" to test content negotiation. The service only produces application/json, so it should return 406.\n\n**Expected:** HTTP 406 Not Acceptable\n**Actual:** HTTP 500 Internal Server Error\n\n**Root Cause:** HttpMediaTypeNotAcceptableException is not handled globally, so it surfaces as a generic 500 instead of a proper 406 response.\n\n**Impact:** API clients that specify Accept: application/xml (common in enterprise integrations) receive a misleading 500 error rather than a clear 406 that would tell them to use application/json instead.","descriptionHtml":"<p><strong>[KNOWN BUG — BUG-SF-007]</strong></p>\n<p><strong>What this test does:</strong><br />\nSends GET /api/v1/fetch/status with &quot;Accept: application/xml&quot; to test content negotiation. The service only produces application/json, so it should return 406.</p>\n<p><strong>Expected:</strong> HTTP 406 Not Acceptable<br />\n<strong>Actual:</strong> HTTP 500 Internal Server Error</p>\n<p><strong>Root Cause:</strong> HttpMediaTypeNotAcceptableException is not handled globally, so it surfaces as a generic 500 instead of a proper 406 response.</p>\n<p><strong>Impact:</strong> API clients that specify Accept: application/xml (common in enterprise integrations) receive a misleading 500 error rather than a clear 406 that would tell them to use application/json instead.</p>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[],"testStage":{"descripti